      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_a7e7f8eb416065372dbbc54eecc8d150">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <altformavail id="aspace_c5298ea364561ce6433dde3203b3d662">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>Golf scrapbooks are available on microfilm (560 frames on 1 reel, 35mm.) from Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library, at cost. Order no. HM184.</p>  
      </altformavail>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4c93970d0593a6f6b63dae11190854da">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of topical files, correspondence, reports and scrapbooks documenting golf at Yale.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
